S. pyogenes Cas9 with inactivating mutations in both cutting domains (HNH and RuvC). Binds to double-stranded DNA as guided by a guide RNA sequence, much like wild-type Cas9 (see C113m), but has no nuclease activity. In conjunction with an appropriate guide RNA, dCas9 can be used to repress transcription, or to sterically block binding of other proteins to the target site.
